                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.01 Manchuria/17: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName corresp="#p_JNT1" type="from"
                            >Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-03-02T11:00:00+08:00"
                            >March 2, 1932—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received March 2—3:15 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>294. Following from American Consul General at Mukden: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“March 1, 3 p.m. The establishment of the new state was announced
                            officially this morning by <persName corresp="#p_CC4">Chang
                                Ching-hui</persName> at his residence at Mukden. After painting a
                            black picture of conditions in Manchuria and China since the
                            establishment of the Republic the proclamation announces the complete
                            severance of relations with the Republic of China and the establishment
                            of the state of Manchoukuo as well as the fundamental principles on
                            which the new state is established including acknowledgment of debt
                            obligations of the territory and the principles of the open door and
                            equal opportunity.</p>
                        <p>It was announced that foreign governments will be notified
                            officially.</p>
                        <p>The Japanese press today state that the inauguration of Pu will occur on
                            March 10th. <persName corresp="#p_MMS1">Myers</persName>.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>For the Minister:<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Perkins</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
